## The Real Question

Hyros is expensive and niche—built for high-ticket info products and coaching businesses. You're here because you want attribution that works for broader use cases, or Hyros's $500+/mo pricing and 6-month commitment don't match your margins.

### Quick Answer

**Want transparent pricing + no lock-in?** Hyros is invite-only with 6-month commitment.
→ **mbuzz** — published pricing ($29-299/mo), free tier, cancel anytime

**Need server-side with model flexibility?** Hyros gives you one view.
→ **mbuzz** — 8 models + custom rules, server-side tracking (95%+ capture)

**Need LTV attribution without the price tag?** Hyros charges $500+/mo.
→ **mbuzz** — LTV attribution on all plans, tracks renewals + upsells to source

**Want broader e-commerce attribution?** Hyros is designed for $500+ AOV only.
→ **Triple Whale** ($129-279/mo) or **mbuzz** (any platform, any AOV)

**Want ML-powered attribution?** Hyros is rule-based.
→ **Northbeam** — $400+/mo, ML fractional

**Need multi-channel including offline?** Hyros focuses on digital ads.
→ **Rockerbox** — podcast/TV tracking + MMM (requires $5M+ ad spend for statistical validity)

### The Uncomfortable Truth

Hyros is good at what it does—tracking high-ticket sales with long consideration windows across phone calls and online touchpoints. The AI optimization claims (20% ROI lift) are compelling if true for your use case.

The issues: invite-only access, opaque pricing, 6-month minimum commitment, and a niche focus that doesn't translate to standard e-commerce or SaaS. If you're selling courses at $2,000+, Hyros might be worth it. If you're doing anything else, you're overpaying for features you don't need.

*If high-ticket info products are your business and you're comfortable with the commitment, vet Hyros in your demo. This guide is for everyone else.*

### Common Reasons to Switch

| Limitation | Impact |
|------------|--------|
| **6-month commitment** | Locked in before you know if it works |
| **Opaque pricing (~$500+/mo)** | No published pricing, invite-only access |
| **High-ticket niche** | Not built for standard e-commerce or SaaS |
| **Limited models** | Basic attribution models, no custom logic |
| **Mixed AI reviews** | Claims 20% ROI lift—results vary |

If any of these resonate, here are your best options.

